reviewText: Don't be scared to buy this DVD. You won't regret it! Jillian isn't as scary as she seems, she wants you to work for the body you want and makes you want to stick with the workout.When you first start workout 1, and you're not used to a lot of physical fitness like me, don't think that you can finish the workout. USE THE PAUSE BUTTON. She and her girls don't stop for water breaks during the 30 minutes so don't be afraid to take a break! Also keep in mind she has a model that does a modified version of the workouts. Don't be scared to do those versions, you'll still get results! This DVD is great if you want to get a good bikini body. If you have a lot of belly fat, I wouldn't expect results fast. I have a small amount around my lower abs and the cardio intervals she puts in really help to burn the fat off while toning the muscle. The DVD focuses more on toning abs than weight loss but you'll lose some for sure with the cardio intervals if you stick with the workouts.
summary: Awesome workout! Great for bikini season

reviewText: A lot of effective moves in this workout, but a lot of really awkwardly pressured ones, as well. There are these jumps you do on all fours in level 3 (she uses this move in Killer Buns and Thighs as well) and it just puts too much pressure on your wrists. It wasn't so bad in the other workout she used this move because you were able to get pressure off your wrists somewhat quickly, but she uses so many moves that apply heavy pressure to the wrists back-to-back, it's hard to enjoy the workout. I have a few sensitive spots on my body from working out hard for many years...the wrists being one of those areas. However, I'm not one to complain about this stuff and will usually just grin and bear it. I just can't do that this time. There was just way too much going on with my wrists, that I was feeling quite a bit of pain in level 3. Let's mix it up a bit more next time, Jillian.

reviewText: I pre-ordered this DVD & was SO excited that it was waiting in my mailbox when I got home yesterday! So I did Level 1 yesterday, then sat down and watched Levels 2 & 3, which I usually do before trying any new workout. While I didn't find it to be quite as cardio-intensive as 6 pack abs (which I LOVE), the exercises are ALL new, mostly non-traditional & tough! The ones that are *somewhat* familiar, have a new twist on them; like instead of doing plank jacks or plank moguls as a cardio interval, we do a hybrid called 'Plank Jack Moguls.'Love that Natalie (from 30-Day Shred, among other Jillian workouts) is back for this one. She's doing the 'Beginner' or 'Modified' workout, but after she shows the modified version, sometimes Jill will hand her a weight or let her show an even more advanced version of the exercise than what the other girl, Nicola (sp?) is doing. You can tell Nat kinda likes that, 'cause she's in great shape...certainly NOT a 'beginner!' Both ladies look GREAT & are very inspirational! Nicola has abs that you will not believe! :-)The only thing I didn't like was the fact that there's a brief plug for Jillian's 360 armband during Level 1 & Level 2 (dont recall if there was one in Level 3). Not sure why; it just bugged me a little. Advertisements elsewhere on the DVD are fine, just not mid-workout (though obviously more people will see it that way)!I'm in pretty good shape & not at all new to Jillian's workouts. I have ALL of her DVDs, which I alternate, working out with them 3 days a week in addition to running 4-6 days a week, averaging 25-30 miles a week. But I was definitely *challenged* by some of the Level 1 exercises. I did modified versions of a few & was able to do advanced versions of others. I look forward to trying out Levels 2 & 3 SOON!
summary: Another great set of workouts from Jillian!

reviewText: I don't know what I like better about this workout than 6 week 6-pack.  Maybe it's the music, the different set, fresh moves, Jillian's usual....ness....I don't know.  I'm used to P90X's Ab Ripper, so I was hoping for a challenge.  Level 1 was pretty basic but good.  I did level 2 between my p90x upper body and ab workouts.  After doing all those chest/shoulder/tricep moves, Jillian's level 2 was a little challenging (a few plank, side plank, pushup moves).  Tomorrow I will do level 3 in between the 2 cardio workouts (hopefully will be a little easier).  So like the title says, if you're used to p90x-type intense moves, these will be significantly easier.  I think these are more for beginner/early-intermediate, not for advanced people looking for a challenge.  She does say "if you want to make it harder, add weights!" which I do (I use 10lbs).  I enjoyed it and will incorporate these ab workouts in future workouts or if I want a little extra ab work.  I thought 6 week 6-pack was hard, but that was before p90x, so 1 star off for not challenging me enough.  These will get you results, if you are consistent and don't eat that crap food.  I just personally hoped for something more challenging.
summary: If you're used to p90x-type ab moves, these are beginner

reviewText: I've been doing many of Jillian's video's the last few years- I started with the Shred and Ripped in 30, and after doing those and losing most of the 35 pounds I needed to lose, I figured it was time to TONE.  So I moved onto 6 weeks to a 6 pack and Killer Buns & Thighs.  All 4 of those video's I LOVE.  I still do them on occasion, I just rotate.  And, just an FYI, I  never do her recommended 5x a week or whatever it is.  I also run and bike, so I alternate days.  I think it's a good combo, as I consider a lot of her workouts more strength training, with definite cardio mixed in.  Anyway, I LOVE 6 weeks to a 6 pack, I love that my heart rate is up, and even after a year and a half of doing it, whenever I pop it in, I still burn nearly 200 calories (keep in mind I'm 5' tall, 115lbs, so for most people you'll burn way more)!  I don't necessarily feel a burn after it, but I have SEEN wonderful results!!  I never thought I'd see my abs again after having kids, but I do now.  :)So...lately I'd been doing No More Trouble Zones(which FYI, has some GREAT ab circuits, where you will definitely feel a burn!), which I also LOVE, since it works ALL my muscles, in addition to Banish Fat Boost Metabolism, since that is great cardio.  However I felt it was time to work on my abs again and wanted to switch it up, since I know that doing the same workout, your body can get used to.  Needless to say I was excited to see this new DVD from Jillian.  I have tried out all the levels and here are my thoughts:#1 Level 1 of Killer Abs is too basic, your heart rate does not get up enough!  I only burn 120 calories, that's nothing for 30 mins.  Level 2 is better, but I forgot to wear my garmin so not sure how many I burn.  Basically, when I do level 1, I am able to do level 2 right after...which is unusual for a Jillian DVD.  But, at least I am burning a bit more.  Level 3 is better- 200 calories.  So, in the future I'll not bother with level 1 and only do 2 and 3...I burn 200 calories doing 6 pack, so anything less is a waste for me.#2 Moves in 6 pack are a bit easier to follow and I feel the instruction Jillian gives a little clearer so you get the hang of it.  I am little bit challenged when it comes to learning new moves, so if it's tricky, I need a clear instruction and a few seconds to get the hang of it.  That's it, I don't' need it slo-mo or anything like that, but this was a little fast for me for such moves...several I'd say are a bit bizarre for sure.I still feel the dvd is a great value- all of her dvd's you can find for under $10, here or in stores.  I normally shop Amazon for video's- great prices!  You can even get sales as low as $7, so you can't beat that- esp. for a video with 3 levels of workouts!!
summary: Not Bad, But Like 6 Week 6 Pack Better
